## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js v18 or higher
- A MongoDB Atlas account (or local MongoDB instance)

### Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/divaaditi101-dev/PulseBoard.git
cd PulseBoard
```

### Backend setup

```bash
cd server
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file inside the `server/` directory:

```
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_atlas_uri
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
PORT=5001
```

Start the backend:

```bash
npm run dev
```

### Frontend setup

Open a new terminal:

```bash
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
```

The frontend runs at `http://localhost:5173` (or `5174` if that port is in use).

---

## Environment Variables

### Server (`server/.env`)

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `MONGO_URI` | MongoDB connection string |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secret key for signing JWT tokens |
| `CLIENT_URL` | Frontend origin for CORS (e.g. `http://localhost:5173`) |
| `PORT` | Port for the Express server (default: 5001) |

### Client (`client/.env`)

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `VITE_API_URL` | Backend API base URL (e.g. `http://localhost:5001/api`) |

---

## Deployment

- **Backend** — deployed on [Render](https://render.com)  
  Root directory: `server` | Start command: `node src/index.js`

- **Frontend** — deployed on [Vercel](https://vercel.com)  
  Root directory: `client` | Framework: Vite

After deploying, set `CLIENT_URL` on Render to your Vercel production URL, and set `VITE_API_URL` on Vercel to your Render backend URL.

---

## API Overview

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Register a new user | No |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login and receive JWT | No |
| POST | `/api/polls` | Create a new poll | Yes |
| GET | `/api/polls/my` | Get all polls by logged-in user | Yes |
| GET | `/api/polls/token/:token` | Get a poll by share token | No |
| POST | `/api/polls/:id/respond` | Submit a response | No |
| GET | `/api/polls/:id/analytics` | Get poll analytics | Yes |
| PATCH | `/api/polls/:id/publish` | Publish a poll | Yes |
| DELETE | `/api/polls/:id` | Delete a poll | Yes |

---

## Design

- Color scheme: Navy (`#0f1f3d`) and Green (`#2ecc8f`)
- Fonts: Syne (headings), DM Sans (body)
- Dark navy sidebar with light main content area

